{
    "id": "elem.6.30",
    "n": 30,
    "type": "proposition",
    "enunciation": "`To cut a given finite straight line in extreme and mean ratio`.",
    "proof": [
        {
            "text": "Let `AB` be the given finite straight line;",
            "refs": [],
            "emphs": [
                "AB"
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "On `AB` let the square `BC` be described; and let there be applied to `AC` the parallelogram `CD` equal to `BC` and exceeding by the figure `AD` similar to `BC`. [elem.6.29]",
            "refs": [
                "elem.6.29"
            ],
            "emphs": [
                "AB",
                "BC",
                "AC",
                "CD",
                "BC",
                "AD",
                "BC"
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Now `BC` is a square;",
            "refs": [],
            "emphs": [
                "BC"
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "And, since `BC` is equal to `CD`, let `CE` be subtracted from each;",
            "refs": [],
            "emphs": [
                "BC",
                "CD",
                "CE"
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "But it is also equiangular with it; therefore in `BF`, `AD` the sides about the equal angles are reciprocally proportional; [elem.6.14]",
            "refs": [
                "elem.6.14"
            ],
            "emphs": [
                "BF",
                "AD"
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "But `FE` is equal to `AB`, and `ED` to `AE`.",
            "refs": [],
            "emphs": [
                "FE",
                "AB",
                "ED",
                "AE"
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Therefore, as `BA` is to `AE`, so is `AE` to `EB`.",
            "refs": [],
            "emphs": [
                "BA",
                "AE",
                "AE",
                "EB"
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "And `AB` is greater than `AE`;",
            "refs": [],
            "emphs": [
                "AB",
                "AE"
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Therefore the straight line `AB` has been cut in extreme and mean ratio at `E`, and the greater segment of it is `AE`. Q. E. F.",
            "refs": [],
            "emphs": [
                "AB",
                "E",
                "AE"
            ]
        }
    ]
}